The National leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, has promised to pay the West African Examinations Council (WAEC) fees of all students sitting for the exams across the country if he is elected president at the 2023 elections. He disclosed this while speaking to a group of party members as seen in a viral video posted on social media, expressing that his administration will break the shackles of poverty, and ignorance. The former Lagos State Governor said, “Your Children’s West African Examinations Council (WAEC) fee will be paid by us, so that no one, no matter how poor is left behind. The symbol of our party is broom, the symbol of my camp is breaking shackles of poverty. To break the shackles of poverty, break the shackles of ignorance. 2023: PVCs Remain Valid, Ignore Tinubu – INEC 2023: Those Expressing Interest Apart From Tinubu Are Agents Of… “We need stability in the country, we need peace. Peace and stopping banditry is extremely important because women are the first victims, are the most vulnerable victims of banditry, violence and instability. “And without, peace and stability, we cannot build the nation as we want. APC is progressing and that is where you should face and mobilise yourselves.”